# Go conventions — distributed-deque

Author is **learning** — prefer skeletons and review over full implementations (see `project-memory.mdc`).

## Layout

```
errors.go, deque.go                 → package distributeddeque (root)
memory/node.go, memory/deque.go    → package memory (doubly-linked list)
memory/deque_test.go               → unit tests beside implementation
memory/ring.go                     → (later) ring-buffer optimization
cmd/queued/main.go                 → queue server; single owner of MemoryDeque
```

| Path | Package | Responsibility |
|------|---------|----------------|
| `errors.go` | `distributeddeque` | `ErrEmpty`, `ErrClosed`; helpers `isEmpty` / `isClosed` |
| `deque.go` | `distributeddeque` | Public `Deque` interface |
| `memory/node.go` | `memory` | `node` struct (`value []byte`, `prev`, `next`); unlink/link helpers |
| `memory/deque.go` | `memory` | `MemoryDeque` — `head`, `tail`, `size`, mutex; O(1) four ops + `Close` |
| `memory/deque_test.go` | `memory` | Table-driven + `-race` tests |
| `memory/ring.go` | `memory` | (later) ring buffer; same method set, different internals |
| `cmd/queued/main.go` | `main` | Only process holding canonical deque; HTTP `/push`, `/pop` |

**Not used:** `list/`, `stream/`, `internal/redis/` (Redis-era layout).

**Imports:** `memory` returns `distributeddeque.ErrEmpty` / `ErrClosed`; root must not import `memory` (avoid cycles). Callers: `memory.NewMemoryDeque()`.

## Interface shape (target)

```go
type Deque interface {
    PushFront(ctx context.Context, value []byte) error
    PushBack(ctx context.Context, value []byte) error
    PopFront(ctx context.Context) ([]byte, error)
    PopBack(ctx context.Context) ([]byte, error)
    Len(ctx context.Context) (int64, error)
    Close() error
}
```

- Every op takes **`context.Context`** first — cancellation must stop blocking waits (v1 pops are non-blocking; blocking/async planned later per README).
- Payload type **`[]byte`** until a generic or typed envelope is designed.

## Errors

- Return **`ErrEmpty`** only for non-blocking pop on empty deque.
- Return **`ErrClosed`** after `Close()`; guard with `sync.Once` or atomic flag on the struct.
- Do not conflate `context.Canceled` and `ErrEmpty`.

## MemoryDeque

- **v1:** doubly-linked nodes (`prev`/`next`), `head`, `tail`, **`size`** for O(1) `Len` — not a plain slice (prepend is O(n)).
- **Later optimization:** ring buffer backing — O(1) both ends, better locality; same public API.
- `container/list` or a custom `node` struct — either is fine; keep mutex on the wrapper.
- One **`sync.Mutex`** per deque; hold for whole push/pop/unlink.
- No network I/O in `memory/` package.
- Copy `[]byte` on pop if callers retain data after the node is unlinked.

## cmd/queued (HTTP server)

- Map `ErrEmpty` → HTTP 204 on `GET /pop`; `ErrClosed` → 503.
- Bound request body (`MaxBytesReader`); copy `[]byte` before `PushBack`.

## Tests

- **Unit:** table-driven tests for empty, single element, both ends, `Close`.
- **Race:** `go test -race ./memory/...`
- **Distribution:** `go run ./cmd/queued` + `curl` for push/pop.
- Name tests by behavior: `TestPopFront_EmptyReturnsErrEmpty`.

## Style

- Match naming: `MemoryDeque`, `NewMemoryDeque`.
- Keep files small; one type per file is fine early on.
- No `init()` side effects; explicit `New*` constructors.
